==Automating plug-ins==

To automate plug-ins in [[Pro Tools]] follow these steps.

'''1.''' First make sure you understand the basic [[Pro Tools:automation modes|Pro Tools automation modes]] and how to [[Pro Tools:Recording automation|record automation in Pro Tools]]

'''2.''' Insert a plug in on a channel.

'''3.''' Click the '''Auto''' button.


[[File:Pro Tools plug in auto button.png]]



'''4.''' In the window that appears choose the parameters you wish to automate and click '''Add'''.





[[File:Pro Tools automating plug ins parameter window.png]]





'''5.''' You can now automate those parameters in your Pro Tools session by setting the respective track to an enabled automation mode. 




[[File:Pro Tools automation mode display.png]]







==Automating all parameters with key command==


To automate all parameters of a plug in hold down '''Control /Option / Command''' and click the '''Auto''' button. This will automatically enable all parameters for automation.

